{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "22", "m": "03", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "12", "M": "25", "S": "34"}}, "news": [{"title": "Vedanta moves NCLAT, challenges NCLT nod to Adani's bid for acquiring Jaiprakash Associates", "para": "Vedanta Group has appealed to the NCLAT against the NCLT's decision. The NCLT had approved Adani Group's bid to acquire Jaiprakash Associates Ltd. Vedanta was also in the race to acquire the company. The Committee of Creditors had previously approved Adani's plan. Jaiprakash Associates has significant assets across real estate, cement, and hospitality.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/vedanta-moves-nclat-challenges-nclt-nod-to-adanis-bid-for-acquiring-jaiprakash-associates/129732622?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-21524/129732622.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Goa PCB issues show-cause notice to housing project in Vasco for discharging untreated sewage", "para": "Goa State Pollution Control Board has issued a show-cause notice to Prabhu Violetta Phase I residential complex in Vasco for discharging untreated sewage. The complex faces potential environmental compensation of Rs 44,50,000 and Rs 12,50,000 for violating pollution norms and operating without valid consent. The board ordered immediate cessation of discharge and daily sewage transport to a public facility.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/goa-pcb-issues-show-cause-notice-to-vasco-housing-project-over-sewage-discharge/129731789?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-98518/129731789.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Bhubaneswar: BMC issues stop-construction order to builder after residents' complaints", "para": "Bhubaneswar Municipal Corporation has halted construction at a Nandan Vihar housing project following resident complaints of unauthorized expansion and ORERA norm violations. Despite the builder's application rejection, work continued. Residents cited issues like unaddressed infrastructure and parking, prompting BMC's intervention and calls for stricter action against the developer.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/bmc-issues-stop-construction-order-to-builder-in-bhubaneswar-over-resident-complaints/129731732?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-44062/129731732.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}]}